    h1#intro Intro
    p
      | Hey there! You&rsquo;re looking at the docs for an Official Bootstrap Theme&mdash;thanks for your purchase! This theme has been lovingly crafted by Bootstrap&rsquo;s founders and friends to help you build awesome projects on the web. Let&rsquo;s dive in.
    p
      | Each theme is designed as it&rsquo;s own toolkit&mdash;a series of well designed, intuitive, and cohesive components&mdash;built on top of Bootstrap. If you&rsquo;ve used Bootstrap itself, you&rsquo;ll find this all super familiar, but with new aesthetics, new components, beautiful and extensive examples, and easy-to-use build tools and documentation.
    p
      | Since this theme is based on Bootstrap, and includes nearly everything Bootstrap itself does, you&rsquo;ll want to give the 
      a(href='http://getbootstrap.com') official project documentation
      |  a once over before continuing. There&rsquo;s also 
      a(href='../bootstrap/') the kitchen sink
      | &mdash;a one-page view of all Bootstrap&rsquo;s components restyled by this theme.
    p
      | For everything else, including compiling and using this Bootstrap theme, read through the docs below.
    p Thanks, and enjoy!
    h1#whats-included What&rsquo;s included
    p
      | Within your Bootstrap theme you&rsquo;ll find the following directories and files, grouping common resources and providing both compiled and minified distribution files, as well as raw source files.
