    h2#theme-source-code Theme source code
    p
      | The 
      code.highlighter-rouge less/
      | , 
      code.highlighter-rouge js/
      | , and 
      code.highlighter-rouge fonts/
      |  directories contain the source code for our CSS, JS, and icon fonts (respectively). Within the 
      code.highlighter-rouge less/
      |  and 
      code.highlighter-rouge js/
      |  directories you&rsquo;ll find two subdirectories:
    ul
      li
        code.highlighter-rouge bootstrap/
        | , which contains the most recently released version of Bootstrap (v3.3.5).
      li
        code.highlighter-rouge custom/
        | , which contains all of the custom components and overrides authored specifically for this theme.
    p
      | The 
      code.highlighter-rouge dist/
      |  folder includes everything above, built into single CSS and JS files that can easily be integrated into your project.
    p
      | The 
      code.highlighter-rouge docs/
      |  folder includes the source code for our documentation, as well as a handful of live examples.
    p
      | The remaining files not specifically mentioned above provide support for packages, license information, and development.
    h1#custom-builds Custom builds
    p
      | Leverage the included source files and 
      code.highlighter-rouge gulpfile.js
      |  to customize your Bootstrap Theme for your exact needs. Change variables, exclude components, and more.
    ul
      li
        code.highlighter-rouge toolkit.less
        |  is the entry point for Less files - to build your own custom build, simply modify your local custom files or edit the includes listed here. Note: some themes also rely on a shared 
        code.highlighter-rouge components.less
        |  file, which you can find imported in your 
        code.highlighter-rouge toolkit.less
        | .
      li
        code.highlighter-rouge variables.less
        |  is home to your theme&rsquo;s variables. Note that your theme&rsquo;s 
        code.highlighter-rouge variables
        |  file depends on and overrides an existing Bootstrap variable file (found in /less/bootstrap/variables.less).
